.SH NAME
bb-pr-comment-delete - Delete a pull request comment


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbb pr comment delete  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Delete a pull request comment. Humans must confirm the exact repository, pull request, and comment unless --yes is provided. Scripts and agents should use --yes together with --no-prompt. Accepts a Bitbucket pull request comment URL directly, or a numeric comment ID together with --pr \&.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for delete

.PP
\fB--host\fP=""
	Bitbucket host to use

.PP
\fB--jq\fP=""
	Filter JSON output using a jq expression

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=""]
	Output JSON with the specified comma-separated fields, or '*' for all fields

.PP
\fB--pr\fP=""
	Parent pull request as an ID or Bitbucket pull request URL; required when the comment target is a numeric ID

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	Bitbucket repository target as , /, or a repository URL

.PP
\fB--workspace\fP=""
	Optional workspace slug used only to disambiguate a bare repository target

.PP
\fB--yes\fP[=false]
	Skip the confirmation prompt


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Do not prompt for missing input, even in an interactive terminal


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bb pr comment delete https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/1#comment-15 --yes
  bb --no-prompt pr comment delete 15 --pr 1 --repo workspace-slug/repo-slug --yes --json '*'
  bb pr comment delete 15 --pr https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/1 --yes
.EE


